Helios OS is an agentic harness — an operating system for AI agents. It governs tool access, budgets, permissions, and human-in-the-loop across 9 framework adapters.

Key directories:
  src/platform/kernel/     — Kernel (permissions, budgets, policies, capabilities, syscall pipeline). BSL 1.1.
  src/forgeos_sdk/         — SDK (runtime, kernel accessor, agent builder, manifest, CLI). Runtime is BSL 1.1, rest Apache 2.0.
  src/platform/            — Platform layer (registry, executor, scheduler, event bus, LLM router, audit, A2A).
  stacks/                  — 9 framework adapters (Helios OS, CrewAI, ADK, LangChain, OpenClaw, Sandbox, Anthropic SDK, Anthropic Managed, OpenAI Agents).
  examples/                — example agents; a few include raw vs governed (agent_raw.py vs agent.py) comparisons.
  dashboard/               — Next.js 15 frontend.
  tests/                   — ~109 test files.

Commands:
  pip install -e ".[dev]"
  PYTHONPATH=. python3 -m pytest
  PYTHONPATH=. python3 -m src.bootstrap --no-auth --dashboard --port 5000

Conventions:
  - Always use python3 and PYTHONPATH=.
  - asyncio_mode = "auto" — no @pytest.mark.asyncio needed
  - Manifests: apiVersion: forgeos/v1 or agentos/v1
  - Tool names: company__*, mcp__server__tool, platform__*, agent__*
  - Every tool call goes through runtime.check_tool() → kernel decision
